column2: Weed cutter cutting weeds.  May be a little stirred up.
Water not as clear.  A lot of suspended particles.
Cleared up since last reading.  Not as weedy as before.
Water very clear- temperature is in the 60s- clear- and sunny.
Water still clear- not much weed cutting.
Hit weeds- could see deeper if no weeds.
Hit weeds- could see deeper if no weeds.
Very clear- most weeds are gone.
Water very cloudy and murky. Yellow scum suspended about 1 foot down.
Water very clear. Less weedy than previous years.
water very clear- not too many weeds.
Water a little murky- some particulate down deep.
Weeds higher- blocked view of disc. Water clear.
Lost sight of disc through weeds.
secchi disk might have been deeper but hit the weeds.
Very weedy since they haven't been able to cut them.
Sunny day today- rained day and night before- water cloudy probably due to rain- and weedy.
level still high- and run off
much better- clear- water looks good
Sunny- Disk lost in weeds at bottom.  Lake clear- looks good.
Sunny- disk hit btoom just as lost in weeds
Sunny- looks good- clear- could see disk to bottom
Water clear- lost in weeds as hit bottom.  Looks good.
Could see clear to bottom.  Lake clear.
Lake not as clear.  Seemed more green than brown this time.  Partly cloudy.
Clear day- lake was weedy.   Water looked good- clear.  Normal levels.  Lake looked good.
Sunny clear day.  The water was clear.  Lost in the weeds just before bottom.  Lake was weedy due to the cutterbeing down a couple of days.
Training on data collection.  DO taken for PB and temp
Nice day- sunny- clear.  Lake looks good.
Lake looks good- clear day- sunny
Clear- sunny.  Lake looks good.  Water level low.

Lake was weedy.  Not cutting had been done due to equipment issues.  Sunny.  The lake level was high.  It had recovered from teh flooding but still high.  There had been a lot of inflow into the lake fromthe flooding causing visibility problems.  The color was dark brown.

Sunny.  There had been significant rain and flooding.  The lake was high. There was quite a bit of runoff from the surrounding farms.  Noticed that when swimming there was quite a bt of silt in teh water that clung to the skin.  The water was murky and dark brown.
Lake looked much better.  There had not been rain for several days.  The water was clearer.  Sunny day.  When swimming did not notice the silt in the water.  Color a little lighter.
Measurement just before weed treatment.  Sunny day little or no wind.  The lake looks godd with some algea blooms.  Water clear- weeds have not yet really started to grow.
Sunnt day- little or no wind.  Lake clear.  Some algea blooms- not much weed growth yet.
Mainly sunny- little or no wind.  Could clearly see disk to bottom.  Lake looked very clear.  Color was lighter than usual- weed load was lighter than usual.
Water was clear.  Could see disk clearly to the bottom.  Sunny day.  The weeds seemed to be better- not as bad as usual.  Did not obstruct view of disk.  Water looked good.
nny day- Lake looks real good.  Some more weeds.  Water clear.  GPS - 43D 45.924M  89D 22.279M

Partly sunny- the lake looked good.  Clear 2 - 3 ft down.  The color to bottom was a light brown- much lighter than in the past.  Could see disk to the bottom.  Air temp 66.2.  There some weeds but not bad.
Lake clear- could see disk to bottom clearly.  Sunny day.  Weather good
Nice day- partly cloudy but some sun.  Windy about 10 mph weeds not bad- somewhat dense at the bottom
Weather was good- phosphorus and clorophyl samples taken.  Disk lost in the weeds just before the bottom.
Partly sunny.  The VanDorn failed.  Unable to obtain samples for DO
Parly cloudy- nice day.  Van Dorhn not working well so free dove and cllected sample from bottom of lake just off the muck.
Helpers:  Geoff Iverson and Joyce Portz
Very windy.  Many weeds below the surface and unable to find a spot anywhere to get an accurate reading without hitting weeds everywhere in the lake.  Mostly sunny skies.
Sunny and slightly windy.  The volunteer week harvestors have been working extremely hard to keep the lake clean of milfoil.
Water appearance was clear.  The color of the water is brown.
